Roma’s head way Both AC Milan and Roma had been looking to sign Dejan Lovren from Liverpool, but Kicker now report that Bayer Leverkusen are on the verge of signing the Croatian centre-back on loan.

Takefusa Kubo has arrived at Palma de Mallorca Airport ahead of a season-long loan at Real Mallorca from Real Madrid. Paulo Dybala continues to be linked with a move to Paris Saint-Germain as the French side view the Argentine as the ideal replacement for Neymar. Sky Sport Italia claim that Leonardo, PSG’s sporting director, has identified Dybala as the superstar who would come in for the Brazilian.


			
